WEBVTT

00:33.282 --> 00:38.810
Welcome back to our study of Proverbs, and we're going to end chapter 7 in this lesson.

00:39.972 --> 00:42.556
A little bit tired.

00:43.117 --> 00:47.624
Someone might say, Brother Paul, the last seven teachings you've had the same shirt on.

00:47.864 --> 00:51.009
That's because I've done all seven today.

00:51.029 --> 01:02.226
I love doing Proverbs, but with my work at HeartCry and the 400 missionaries we have around the world, I stay pretty busy.

01:02.658 --> 01:06.662
I can't escape and come down here as frequently as I would like to.

01:07.163 --> 01:12.849
But when I do have an opportunity, I like to teach several lessons.

01:13.470 --> 01:15.872
And so this will be the last lesson of the day.

01:15.932 --> 01:19.676
And we will finish up Proverbs 7.

01:20.277 --> 01:23.380
I want you to know this is a joy for me.

01:23.420 --> 01:28.946
And even though it's not that formal, I'm kind of

01:29.314 --> 01:37.183
teaching it in the same way that I taught Proverbs to my children over and over, over a period of many, many years.

01:38.184 --> 01:50.217
And I do believe young people that if you will, if you'll study the book of Proverbs as well as the rest of Scripture, God will, well, he'll use it to transform your life.

01:50.998 --> 01:54.842
He'll use it to transform your life.

01:54.862 --> 01:58.706
Now, let's read Proverbs 7, verse 24,

01:59.298 --> 02:00.780
through the end of the chapter.

02:01.821 --> 02:06.326
Now therefore my sons, listen to me and pay attention to the words of my mouth.

02:07.547 --> 02:10.090
Do not let your heart turn aside to her ways.

02:10.410 --> 02:12.512
Do not stray into her paths.

02:13.573 --> 02:19.039
For many are the victims she has cast down and numerous are all her slain.

02:19.900 --> 02:26.687
Her house is in the way of shield descending to the chambers of death.

02:27.388 --> 02:27.789
All right.

02:28.690 --> 02:29.170
So

02:29.602 --> 02:30.824
Let's go to the Lord in prayer.

02:32.766 --> 02:49.048
Father, I pray that you would give ears to hear and that Lord there, there would be great fear of sin and great reverence for you.

02:50.891 --> 02:59.282
Father, communicate through your spirit what no man can communicate to another.

03:00.130 --> 03:02.893
illumine the mind, renew the mind.

03:04.535 --> 03:15.927
And Lord, if there's someone in this that is listening to this that does not know your son, I pray that they would realize that he is the only answer.

03:17.869 --> 03:19.791
And in him alone is found salvation.

03:21.373 --> 03:22.174
In Jesus name.

03:23.936 --> 03:24.256
Amen.

03:25.458 --> 03:25.938
So

03:27.426 --> 03:33.172
Of course, verse 24, now therefore my sons listen to me and pay attention to the words of my mouth.

03:34.333 --> 03:54.194
Now therefore means that he's linking this to what preceded it and what preceded a description of how horrific our lives can be if we give ourselves to sin, that it is a very, very serious thing here.

03:54.882 --> 03:56.044
that we have before us.

03:56.224 --> 04:02.395
We see a young man who fell into temptation and literally destroyed himself.

04:03.437 --> 04:09.388
Now don't think this is unique because many throughout history and many today are doing the same.

04:10.550 --> 04:13.375
Notice that he says, listen to me, pay attention to me.

04:15.018 --> 04:16.039
It's double speech.

04:16.180 --> 04:17.522
It's just he's

04:17.602 --> 04:23.592
emphasizing, piling one phrase upon another to say, I plead with you, listen to me.

04:24.032 --> 04:34.529
It's like a father grabbing his son by the collar or putting his daughter's face in his hands and saying, please, please, I beg you, listen to me.

04:34.910 --> 04:39.597
This is a matter of life and death of heaven and hell.

04:40.398 --> 04:40.779
All right.

04:41.901 --> 04:45.106
Now it says, do not turn

04:45.826 --> 04:47.449
aside to her ways.

04:48.611 --> 05:02.133
See, what we're assuming here is that, first of all, this person was walking in the path of righteousness, but turned aside and joined her in her ways.

05:03.396 --> 05:09.586
And so the world is constantly standing outside the path of righteousness.

05:10.274 --> 05:12.517
that the scripture marks out for us.

05:12.597 --> 05:19.848
The world is constantly standing to one side, just like in Bunyan's Pilgrim Progress, calling and calling.

05:20.169 --> 05:24.215
Step aside, step aside, turn to me, turn to me.

05:24.555 --> 05:28.922
Don't keep your eyes focused on eternity.

05:29.823 --> 05:32.767
Keep your feet in the paths of righteousness.

05:33.288 --> 05:36.232
And you do that through the Word of God and prayer.

05:36.673 --> 05:37.394
Do not

05:37.538 --> 05:44.687
turn your heart aside to her ways because the moment you do, your feet are going to turn aside to her ways.

05:45.087 --> 05:47.170
Do not stray into her path.

05:48.612 --> 05:53.718
Don't try to live in some sort of broad way moving back and forth.

05:54.339 --> 06:01.848
Jesus was very clear that the way to eternal life is narrow and it is marked out by the Word of God.

06:02.148 --> 06:03.410
It is not marked out

06:04.002 --> 06:07.526
by the opinions of man and most certainly the opinions of culture.

06:08.467 --> 06:09.708
Focus on the word.

06:09.828 --> 06:10.689
Know the word.

06:10.809 --> 06:15.033
Mark each step of your life by what you know from scripture.

06:16.815 --> 06:21.940
Then he says, now here's the big warning and you need to listen to it.

06:23.502 --> 06:24.743
Let me just summarize it.

06:27.326 --> 06:31.570
Her house is a tomb and it's filled full.

06:31.714 --> 06:51.376
sends houses a tomb and it is filled full of billions and billions and billions of corpses of men who did not listen to counsel of women and youth who did not listen to God's counsel and end up in a house of death.

06:52.358 --> 06:58.344
So he says, for many are the victims she has cast down.

06:58.404 --> 06:59.826
The word here literally

07:00.002 --> 07:02.205
is many are the pierced ones.

07:03.708 --> 07:10.979
They've been pierced through like an arrow through a liver, dying in agony.

07:11.319 --> 07:19.331
It refers to somewhat, to some, to being fatally wounded, pierced, pierced through.

07:21.034 --> 07:29.266
In 1 Timothy 6, 10, Paul writes, for the love of money is a root of all sorts of evil and somebody longing for it.

07:29.698 --> 07:37.672
have wandered away from the faith and pierced themselves with many griefs."

07:37.692 --> 07:42.701
Now, here he's talking about wealth, but we could substitute any manner of temptation here.

07:43.162 --> 07:54.162
Not just the temptation for money or the love of money, but the temptation of the lusts of the flesh, the temptations of fame, the temptations of this world, the temptations of the devil,

07:55.938 --> 07:59.482
and some by longing for it have wandered away.

07:59.842 --> 08:11.035
The moment, the moment you begin to notice in you a desire for the things of the world, crucify it, hate it, count it dead.

08:11.376 --> 08:20.847
If necessary, go to your parents, go to the pastor and say, this is starting to take root in me, help me, deal with it quickly.

08:20.887 --> 08:23.890
If you drink poison,

08:25.314 --> 08:32.405
You would not say, okay, maybe in a month, I'll go to the doctor or go to the emergency.

08:32.465 --> 08:42.680
No, if you were shot, if you ran yourself through with a spike, you'd say, take me immediately to deal with this problem.

08:43.021 --> 08:48.229
When you see sin, deal with it immediately or it will grab you.

08:48.449 --> 08:51.634
When you start seeing the desire grow in you,

08:52.354 --> 08:59.906
The moment you see that, you know, I don't know what you'd want to call it, a seed or an acorn, start taking root, get it out of there.

09:00.567 --> 09:20.658
Get it out of there at all costs because longing will eventually turn into walking and wandering into a path of death which leads to piercing, which leads to, well, eternal ruin.

09:22.018 --> 09:28.610
Now, so he says, many are the victims she has cast down.

09:30.814 --> 09:34.321
It can also be interpreted that she has caused to fall.

09:36.345 --> 09:38.689
The world and the devil.

09:40.292 --> 09:41.895
Now listen to me very carefully.

09:43.057 --> 09:45.682
The world and the devil have a trophy room.

09:53.186 --> 10:05.658
When we kill a deer sometimes, if it's big enough, we hang it on the wall or a turkey tail and a turkey beard, we hang it on the wall, a trophy room.

10:06.819 --> 10:09.161
I killed this one when I was 12.

10:09.541 --> 10:11.503
I killed this one when I was 20.

10:12.004 --> 10:13.805
I killed this one with a long bow.

10:14.326 --> 10:15.867
These are my trophies.

10:16.608 --> 10:22.834
Well, you need to know the world and the devil have a trophy room as big as the world.

10:24.034 --> 10:29.659
and many are there and they will never leave.

10:29.679 --> 10:32.702
And so it says here, many are the victims.

10:32.802 --> 10:36.666
She has cast down and numerous are all her slain.

10:37.207 --> 10:39.589
Now see, it's just saying the same thing, isn't it?

10:40.229 --> 10:43.032
For many are the victims that she's cast down.

10:43.412 --> 10:44.253
That's one statement.

10:44.473 --> 10:53.522
Now he's going to repeat it and say it again, just a different way for added emphasis and numerous are all her

10:53.826 --> 10:54.487
slain.

10:55.368 --> 11:02.059
This word for slain oftentimes implies a ruthless violence.

11:05.324 --> 11:09.470
There is a violence in this world, two boxers fighting.

11:10.412 --> 11:12.796
There's a degree of violence.

11:14.118 --> 11:20.427
But I've seen men around the world whose violence, there was no mercy.

11:21.169 --> 11:22.130
It was vile.

11:22.498 --> 11:23.860
It was disgusting.

11:25.603 --> 11:26.744
It was terrifying.

11:28.827 --> 11:34.095
You look them in the eye and there's nothing there, but just evil.

11:34.896 --> 11:36.118
That's the idea here.

11:37.180 --> 11:38.041
That's the idea.

11:38.462 --> 11:41.526
Not just slain, they didn't die in their sleep.

11:43.329 --> 11:52.402
No, they were violently slain by sin, violently slain by the devil, violently slain by

11:52.482 --> 11:53.003
the world.

11:53.624 --> 11:57.329
Literally, this text, verse 26, we could do it this way.

11:58.050 --> 12:09.205
Many are the pierced or mortally wounded that she has caused to fall and numerous are those whom she has violently slain.

12:10.546 --> 12:10.887
Okay?

12:11.848 --> 12:13.050
That's what we're dealing with here.

12:13.811 --> 12:14.832
That's what we're dealing with.

12:14.852 --> 12:17.496
And you may sit there right now and laugh.

12:18.597 --> 12:22.002
You may think, Oh, yeah, I know.

12:23.810 --> 12:26.553
But you won't be laughing in the end.

12:27.594 --> 12:31.197
You'll be saying, why did I not listen to counsel?

12:31.337 --> 12:35.121
Why did I not turn before it was too late?

12:35.661 --> 12:37.823
And now it is too late.

12:40.005 --> 12:48.373
Now, verse 27, her house is the way to shield, descending to the chambers of death.

12:48.854 --> 12:53.138
Look how she describes her house in verses 16 and 17.

12:53.250 --> 12:57.656
Look how she, look how sin describes its house.

12:57.676 --> 12:59.778
Look how the devil describes his house.

12:59.818 --> 13:03.623
Look at how the world describes the house.

13:04.384 --> 13:11.273
Verse 16, I have spread my couch with coverings with colored linens of Egypt.

13:11.293 --> 13:16.279
I have sprinkled my bed with mirth, alloys, alloys and cinnamon.

13:17.200 --> 13:21.746
It looks beautiful and it smells beautiful.

13:23.074 --> 13:26.960
But the coverings are covering up corpses.

13:28.602 --> 13:34.050
And the perfume is just masking the scent of rotten flesh.

13:34.772 --> 13:46.649
Because when you get over to verse 27, her house is the way to shield descending to the chambers of death.

13:49.854 --> 13:52.498
When I was a boy, you know,

13:53.410 --> 14:00.499
I can remember one time where my dad told me he said, he said, boy, get up, get the tractor.

14:01.179 --> 14:03.963
We have a cow out in a certain field.

14:04.423 --> 14:07.587
And it was standing too close to a tree during a thunderstorm.

14:07.647 --> 14:08.969
And it was struck by lightning.

14:10.531 --> 14:14.676
And he didn't find it until like three or four days after it happened.

14:14.696 --> 14:20.082
He said, go out there, chain them, drag them with the tractor to the dump.

14:22.754 --> 14:38.171
I can still, I remember the things that happened, what it took for me to drag that animal to wear this dump where it was for dead bodies of animals, of cattle that had died.

14:39.472 --> 14:42.296
And it was just hellish.

14:43.617 --> 14:51.826
It was, you know, you'd wear a bandana around your face, hoping that it would kind of, you know, it would cut the scent

14:53.442 --> 14:54.904
And that's what we're talking about.

14:55.364 --> 15:00.491
Many of you, you know, your, your lives, your lives have been so isolated.

15:00.511 --> 15:07.700
You can't understand what I'm talking about, but it's a rot and a stink unlike anything you could ever imagine.

15:09.682 --> 15:10.724
And that's what he's talking about.

15:10.744 --> 15:14.508
She describes her house as beautiful, as fragrant.

15:15.349 --> 15:19.154
It's nothing but rotting corpses.

15:19.778 --> 15:29.230
In verse 27, we see, I've written here, it's not a house of pleasure or even a house of entertainment or like Bunyan's vanity fair.

15:29.570 --> 15:30.331
It's not that.

15:30.611 --> 15:31.573
It's a mausoleum.

15:32.654 --> 15:33.435
It's a vault.

15:33.695 --> 15:37.159
It's a crypt filled with rotting corpses.

15:37.259 --> 15:40.363
Again, remember what I said, the propaganda looks great.

15:41.144 --> 15:49.074
But when you pass through the door, it may still look great until that door slams behind you and then they turn the lights on.

15:49.954 --> 15:54.761
and you see that you're among corpses and you have become one.

15:59.247 --> 16:03.453
Her house I wrote here is like a spider's lair.

16:03.733 --> 16:12.605
I don't know if you've ever read the Lord of the Rings and those works, Fellowship of the Rings, Return of the King, Shilob.

16:13.867 --> 16:18.994
When you read about, you know, Frodo going in there,

16:19.074 --> 16:20.496
going into those tunnels.

16:20.716 --> 16:28.425
It's terrifying trying to escape the rot of all the corpses that had been struck by that spider.

16:29.686 --> 16:36.133
That's the idea filled with the rotting corpses of all who have given in to temptation.

16:37.495 --> 16:39.617
Now, we're ending this chapter.

16:41.419 --> 16:43.622
It's kind of dark.

16:45.544 --> 16:47.506
Well, should I hide that from you?

16:48.450 --> 16:50.353
Should I let you find that out yourself?

16:51.495 --> 16:52.176
I don't think so.

16:55.802 --> 17:07.640
If I truly care, if your parents truly care, if your preacher truly cares and is not a coward, they're all going to warn you.

17:09.944 --> 17:13.910
There are so many beautiful things about life and relationships.

17:14.010 --> 17:16.594
God has given so much grace

17:17.218 --> 17:22.866
that we even live in a world that still has beauty is a demonstration of God's kindness.

17:23.266 --> 17:23.967
It truly is.

17:25.509 --> 17:31.197
But no, there is a dark side and it is terrible.

17:31.558 --> 17:31.998
Let me give you up.

17:32.018 --> 17:33.240
There's a good illustration.

17:33.280 --> 17:34.822
It doesn't fit perfectly.

17:35.283 --> 17:37.546
It's in Isaiah 14, 9 through 11.

17:38.327 --> 17:41.491
It's sometimes applied to the king of Babylon, sometimes to the devil.

17:41.992 --> 17:46.418
But it's this person who has fallen

17:47.426 --> 17:53.433
and is now being received in shield or in the grave or in death.

17:54.594 --> 18:01.461
And it says, shield from beneath is excited over you to meet you when you come, the grave.

18:03.724 --> 18:10.291
Like almost like portrayed here is some sort of animal devouring, excited about a prey.

18:11.352 --> 18:13.755
It arouses for you the spirits of the dead.

18:14.135 --> 18:16.658
So there's just countless other

18:17.570 --> 18:20.213
ruined lives there.

18:22.094 --> 18:23.456
And you're going to join them.

18:24.156 --> 18:25.237
All the leaders of the earth.

18:25.297 --> 18:27.600
It doesn't matter how powerful you are.

18:27.980 --> 18:29.241
There is a payday someday.

18:30.643 --> 18:35.227
If you neglect the Lord, you neglect the Word.

18:35.547 --> 18:36.809
You reject Christ.

18:37.910 --> 18:46.578
You're going to join a countless multitude of individuals, great and small, that will live

18:47.426 --> 18:54.093
eternally in death, maybe exist would be a better term in death.

18:55.475 --> 18:58.919
It raises all the kings of the nations from their thrones.

18:59.719 --> 19:07.668
They will all respond and say to you, even you have been made weak as we, you have become like us.

19:08.970 --> 19:16.658
Can you imagine being met in the gates of hell by a multitude

19:17.410 --> 19:21.135
of its inhabitants saying to you, Welcome.

19:23.178 --> 19:24.640
You are now like us.

19:25.321 --> 19:26.583
There is no life here.

19:27.083 --> 19:28.345
There is no escape.

19:30.789 --> 19:35.796
In verse 11, your pompt and the music of your harps have been brought down to shield.

19:37.618 --> 19:46.130
Listen, I love laughter and I love

19:46.370 --> 19:58.563
joy and I love my friendships and I love when we get together here in the office and in church and I love all kinds of things, hunting camps and running around with my buddies.

20:02.468 --> 20:08.855
But one day all the pomp and all the music and all the laughter is going to die.

20:09.135 --> 20:10.136
I'm going to die.

20:10.616 --> 20:12.018
You're going to die.

20:12.738 --> 20:17.283
And the question comes, when we die, everything here is gone.

20:20.206 --> 20:29.477
We'll either enter into a glory that we can't even begin to comprehend, or we'll enter into a darkness and a death that no man can understand.

20:31.379 --> 20:33.141
But one day all the harps will stop.

20:33.882 --> 20:35.223
All the dancing will stop.

20:35.804 --> 20:37.105
All the laughter will stop.

20:38.187 --> 20:41.170
All the beauty and all the riches will be gone.

20:42.242 --> 20:49.532
And then it said, maggots are spread out as your bed beneath you and worms are your covering.

20:50.894 --> 20:55.019
Jesus talked about a place where the worm does not die.

20:58.444 --> 21:00.406
Some people say, well, that's metaphor.

21:01.348 --> 21:04.893
Well, let's say for a moment it is.

21:07.476 --> 21:11.922
I think it's far more realistic than what people believe, but let's just say for a moment,

21:12.002 --> 21:12.943
that that's metaphor.

21:13.424 --> 21:15.928
What you need to understand is that metaphor is weak.

21:16.529 --> 21:22.077
Whatever's waiting, you in hell is far worse than what that metaphor is communicating.

21:23.519 --> 21:27.045
There is no language or word or metaphor to describe heaven.

21:27.766 --> 21:30.730
There is no word or metaphor language to describe hell.

21:31.992 --> 21:35.778
You say, Brother Paul, I'm trying to scare us.

21:36.298 --> 21:38.922
No, I'm trying to put fear in you.

21:38.982 --> 21:39.744
There's a difference.

21:40.645 --> 21:41.426
It's much more.

21:41.986 --> 21:42.527
profound.

21:43.729 --> 21:50.379
When I used to take new guys into the jungle, I would say, now listen to me.

21:51.120 --> 21:53.584
There are some things you should not do.

21:53.844 --> 21:56.248
You must not do.

21:56.809 --> 21:59.713
And there are certain things that you must do.

22:00.374 --> 22:01.756
And this is not a game.

22:02.297 --> 22:03.359
It's not a movie.

22:04.701 --> 22:06.003
All right, it's the same way.

22:06.644 --> 22:08.306
We've gone through chapter seven.

22:09.314 --> 22:14.561
And in many ways, it's been a very dark and solemn journey.

22:17.084 --> 22:32.885
We come out on the other side with this, fear sin, reverence God and run to Jesus Christ and stay there and make His Word the lamp because it is the only lamp.

22:34.868 --> 22:39.314
Make His Word the lamp to your feet and you'll do well.

22:40.290 --> 22:40.971
You'll do well.

22:42.572 --> 22:43.093
Let's pray.

22:46.356 --> 22:47.217
Father, thank you.

22:49.079 --> 22:57.147
Oh, dear God, please work through these messages.

23:00.790 --> 23:06.136
I have no desire for eloquence or to talk for the sake of talking.

23:07.737 --> 23:08.658
Use this, Lord.

23:09.634 --> 23:16.110
for the benefit of many in Jesus' name.

23:16.130 --> 23:16.471
Amen.

23:17.674 --> 23:23.207
Well, God bless you and hopefully next time we will be in chapter eight.

23:23.729 --> 23:25.894
And there's a lot of good there.

23:26.836 --> 23:27.538
So God bless.

